text: Abdel-Aziz bin Habtour (, born 8 August 1955) is a Yemeni politician. He was the Governor of Aden during the Houthi takeover in Yemen. He is a member of the General People's Congress. In 2016, he became the Prime Minister of Yemen, however this has been disputed since 2018. ==References== Category:1955 births Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of Yemen Category:Current national leaders
title: Abdel-Aziz bin Habtour
